# RAG Pipeline Architecture

## Hard Constraints

- Custom pipeline — NO LangChain, NO LlamaIndex
- Multi-language support: COBOL preprocessor + Fortran preprocessor, dispatched by file extension
- Chunking must respect language-specific boundaries (COBOL paragraphs, Fortran subroutines)
- Chunk size: adaptive 64–768 tokens on structural boundaries
- Embeddings: batch mode via Voyage Code 2 (128 texts per API call, 1536 dimensions)

## Vector Storage

- Qdrant with payload indexes on: `paragraph_name`, `division`, `file_path`, `language`, `codebase`
- Single shared collection for all codebases
- Metadata filtering for per-codebase queries

## Retrieval

- Hybrid search (dense + sparse/BM25) via Qdrant native support
- Query-adaptive weighting: identifier queries → 0.6 BM25, semantic queries → 0.7 dense
- Re-ranking: metadata-based first (free), then Cohere cross-encoder second

## Context Assembly

- Dynamic token budget (5,000 tokens total)
- Top-1 result gets hierarchical expansion (up to 2,000 tokens)
- Remaining chunks fill 3,000 token breadth budget in relevance order

## Generation

- Structured language-aware system prompt with language + feature inserts
- Confidence output: HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
- All answers must include file:line citations
- All 8 features implemented as composable prompt + retrieval strategies
